#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pi-tv-bu-vb-pc31"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:0.4"
msgid "Bhojanavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 31"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:0.5"
msgid "31. Āvasathapiṇḍasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on alms-meals at public guest houses"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:0.6"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.70, pts-cs-bu-pc31.1, pts-vp-en.2.303, ms2V_664
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyā avidūre aññatarassa pūgassa āvasathapiṇḍo paññatto hoti."
msgstr "At that time a certain association was preparing an alms-meal at a public guest house not far from Sāvatthī."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.3"
msgid "Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pavisitvā piṇḍaṃ alabhamānā āvasathaṃ agamaṃsu."
msgstr "One morning the monks from the group of six robed up, took their bowl and robe, and entered Sāvatthī for alms. Not getting anything, they went to that public guest house."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.4"
msgid "Manussā—“cirassampi bhadantā āgatā”ti sakkaccaṃ parivisiṃsu."
msgstr "And because it was long since they had been there, people served them respectfully."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.5"
msgid "Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū dutiyampi divasaṃ … pe … tatiyampi divasaṃ pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pavisitvā piṇḍaṃ alabhamānā āvasathaṃ gantvā bhuñjiṃsu."
msgstr "For a second and third day those monks did the same thing."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.6"
msgid "Atha kho chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—"
msgstr "Then they thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.7"
msgid "“kiṃ mayaṃ karissāma ārāmaṃ gantvā."
msgstr "“What’s the point of returning to the monastery?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.8"
msgid "Hiyyopi idheva āgantabbaṃ bhavissatī”ti,"
msgstr "Tomorrow we’ll just have to come back here.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.9"
msgid "tattheva anuvasitvā anuvasitvā āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjanti."
msgstr "And so they stayed  on and on right there, eating alms at the guest house."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.10"
msgid "Titthiyā apasakkanti."
msgstr "And the ascetics of other sects departed."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.11"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People then complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.12"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā anuvasitvā anuvasitvā āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjissanti."
msgstr "“How can these Sakyan ascetics stay on and on, eating alms at the guest house?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.13"
msgid "Nayimesaññeva āvasathapiṇḍo paññatto;"
msgstr "We don’t prepare the alms-food just for them;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.14"
msgid "sabbesaññeva āvasathapiṇḍo paññatto”ti."
msgstr "we prepare it for everyone.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_665
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.15"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.16"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.17"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.18"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū anuvasitvā anuvasitvā āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six stay on and on, eating alms at a public guest house?” …"

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.304
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.19"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, anuvasitvā anuvasitvā āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.20"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.21"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.22"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, anuvasitvā anuvasitvā āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjissatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you stay on and on, eating alms at a public guest house?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.23"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.24"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.24a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_666
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.25"
msgid "“Eko āvasathapiṇḍo bhuñjitabbo. Tato ce uttari bhuñjeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk eats more than one alms-meal at a public guest house, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc4, ms2V_667
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:1.26"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc5, pts-cs-bu-pc31.2, ms2V_668
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā sāriputto kosalesu janapade sāvatthiṃ gacchanto yena aññataro āvasatho tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr "Soon afterwards Venerable Sāriputta was traveling in the Kosalan country towards Sāvatthī when he came to a public guest house."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:2.2"
msgid "Manussā—“cirassampi thero āgato”ti sakkaccaṃ parivisiṃsu."
msgstr "Because it was long since he had been there, people served him respectfully."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:2.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa bhuttāvissa kharo ābādho uppajji, nāsakkhi tamhā āvasathā pakkamituṃ."
msgstr "After he had eaten, Sāriputta became severely ill, and he was not able to leave that guest house."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:2.4"
msgid "Atha kho te manussā dutiyampi divasaṃ āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "On the second day, too, those people said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:2.5"
msgid "“bhuñjatha, bhante”ti."
msgstr "“Eat, Venerable.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:2.6"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto—"
msgstr "But since he knew that"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:2.7"
msgid "“bhagavatā paṭikkhittaṃ anuvasitvā anuvasitvā āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjitun”ti kukkuccāyanto na paṭiggahesi;"
msgstr "the Master had prohibited eating alms at a public guest house after staying on and on, and because he was afraid of wrongdoing, he did not accept."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:2.8"
msgid "chinnabhatto ahosi."
msgstr "As a consequence he missed his meal."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: ms2V_669
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:2.9"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "When he arrived at Sāvatthī, he told the monks what had happened,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:2.10"
msgid "Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "and they in turn told the Master."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:2.11"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. HTML: <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:2.12"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānena bhikkhunā anuvasitvā anuvasitvā āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow a sick monk to stay on at a public guest house and eat alms there."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:2.13"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "” And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:2.13a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_670
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:2.14"
msgid "“Agilānena bhikkhunā eko āvasathapiṇḍo bhuñjitabbo."
msgstr "‘If a monk who is not sick eats more than one alms-meal at a public guest house,"

#. VAR: uttari → uttariṃ (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:2.15"
msgid "Tato ce uttari bhuñjeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, pts-cs-bu-pc31.3.1, ms2V_671
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.1.1"
msgid "Agilāno nāma"
msgstr "Who is not sick:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.1.2"
msgid "sakkoti tamhā āvasathā pakkamituṃ."
msgstr "he is able to leave that public guest house."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_672
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.1.3"
msgid "Gilāno nāma"
msgstr "Who is sick:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.1.4"
msgid "na sakkoti tamhā āvasathā pakkamituṃ."
msgstr "he is not able to leave that public guest house."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, pts-vp-pli4.71, pts-vp-en.2.305, ms2V_673
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.1.5"
msgid "Āvasathapiṇḍo nāma"
msgstr "Alms-meal at a public guest house:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.1.6"
msgid "pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññataraṃ bhojanaṃ—"
msgstr "as much as one needs of any of the five staple foods, prepared for the general public,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.1.7"
msgid "sālāya vā maṇḍape vā rukkhamūle vā ajjhokāse vā anodissa yāvadattho paññatto hoti."
msgstr "in a hall, under a roof-cover, at the foot of a tree, or out in the open."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.1.8"
msgid "Agilānena bhikkhunā sakiṃ bhuñjitabbo."
msgstr "A monk who is not sick may eat there once."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.1.9"
msgid "Tato ce uttari “bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he receives food beyond that with the intention of eating it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.1.10"
msgid "Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc11, pts-cs-bu-pc31.3.2, ms2V_674
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.2.1"
msgid "Agilāno agilānasaññī tatuttari āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If he is not sick, and he perceives himself as not sick, and he eats more than one alms-meal at a public guest house, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.2.2"
msgid "Agilāno vematiko tatuttari āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If he is not sick, but he is unsure of it, and he eats more than one alms-meal at a public guest house, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.2.3"
msgid "Agilāno gilānasaññī tatuttari āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If he is not sick, but he perceives himself as sick, and he eats more than one alms-meal at a public guest house, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_675
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.2.4"
msgid "Gilāno agilānasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he is sick, but he perceives himself as not sick, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.2.5"
msgid "Gilāno vematiko āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he is sick, but he is unsure if he is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.2.6"
msgid "Gilāno gilānasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If he is sick, and he perceives himself as sick, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc13, pts-cs-bu-pc31.3.3, ms2V_676
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.3.2"
msgid "gilānassa,"
msgstr "if he is sick;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.3.3"
msgid "agilāno sakiṃ bhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he is not sick and he eats once;"

# NOTE: The commentary explain this as: “Or going means: whoever is going, if he eats one day on the road and one day at the place he has gone to, there is no offense. The same method applies for one who is coming. After going, even when returning, he may eat one day on the road and one day at the place returned to.” _Gacchanto vāti yo gacchanto antarāmagge ekadivasaṃ gataṭṭhāne ca ekadivasaṃ bhuñjati, tassāpi anāpatti. Āgacchantepi eseva nayo. Gantvā paccāgacchantopi antarāmagge ekadivasaṃ āgataṭṭhāne ca ekadivasaṃ bhuñjituṃ labhati._
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.3.4"
msgid "gacchanto, vā āgacchanto vā bhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he eats while coming or going;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.3.5"
msgid "sāmikā nimantetvā bhojenti,"
msgstr "if he eats after being invited by the owners;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.3.6"
msgid "odissa paññatto hoti,"
msgstr "if the food is prepared for him;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.3.7"
msgid "na yāvadattho paññatto hoti,"
msgstr "if there is not as much as he needs;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.3.8"
msgid "pañca bhojanāni ṭhapetvā sabbattha anāpatti,"
msgstr "if it is anything apart from the five staple foods;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.3.9"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.3.10"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc14, ms2V_677
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc31:3.3.11"
msgid "Āvasathapiṇḍasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr "The first rule, the training rule on alms-meals at public guest houses, is finished."


